           =20
<div class=3D"ad-free">
    <p>
        The Affine cipher is a type of monoalphabetic substitution cipher w=
here each letter is mapped using a
        mathematical function (<code>E(x) =3D (ax + b) mod m</code>). This =
is a tool to encode and decode Affine ciphers
        interactively as well as a guide to understand how it works.
    </p>
    <h5>Related ciphers</h5>
    <ul>
        <li><a href=3D"https://www.boxentriq.com/code-breaking/caesar-ciphe=
r" class=3D"greentext-link" data-q-internal-link=3D"true">Caesar cipher</a>=
 =E2=80=94 the Affine cipher behaves like a Caesar cipher
            when <code>a =3D 1</code>.</li>
        <li><a href=3D"https://www.boxentriq.com/code-breaking/substitution=
-cipher" class=3D"greentext-link" data-q-internal-link=3D"true">Substitutio=
n cipher</a> =E2=80=94 a more general monoalphabetic
            cipher.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        Are you unsure about the cipher type? Use the <a href=3D"https://ww=
w.boxentriq.com/code-breaking/cipher-identifier" class=3D"greentext-link" d=
ata-q-internal-link=3D"true">Cipher Identifier</a>
        to find the right tool.
    </p>
</div>
<div class=3D"ad-free">
